crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
This code constitutes a library for implementing and interacting with the Microsoft Remote Procedure Call (MSRPC) protocol. It defines various MSRPC packet structures and constants for message types, flags, authentication mechanisms, and status codes. The library supports both client-side (`DCERPC_v5`) and server-side (`DCERPCServer`) operations.

The client-side implementation handles MSRPC session management, including binding to interfaces, altering contexts, and sending/receiving RPC requests and responses. It incorporates advanced authentication capabilities using NTLM, NETLOGON, and Kerberos, with support for packet signing and sealing based on specified authentication levels. It also manages packet fragmentation for efficient data transfer.

The server-side component (`DCERPCServer`) provides functionality to listen for incoming MSRPC connections, process bind requests, and dispatch RPC operations to registered callbacks based on interface UUIDs and operation numbers. It also handles the fragmentation and reassembly of packets for incoming and outgoing data.

The code primarily focuses on the serialization, deserialization, and logical flow of the MSRPC protocol, enabling programmatic interaction with Windows-based RPC services.
